<div style='width:500px' >
<ul>
<li>
Sintax for return a default fixed value: returnValue('value to return'). 
Example: returnValue('myValue')
</li>
<li>
Sintax for return the value of a single-value user profile attribute: 
getSingleValueProfileAttribute(name of profile attribute). Example: getSingleValueProfileAttribute(branch)
</li>
<li>
Sintax for return the values of a multi-value user profile attribute as a unique string:
getMultiValueProfileAttribute(name of profile attribute, prefix, splitter, suffix). 
Example: getMultiValueProfileAttribute(branches, 'in (', ';', ')')
This method will return a string like this: prefix+(list of values separated by the splitter)+suffix
</li>
<li>
Sintax for a generic script:
groovy script which returns an xml string structured in a predefined manner. 
Look at the bottom of the sintax box to learn the xml structure. 
Inside the script it's possible to use profile attributes as a variable simply writing the name of the attribute.
</li>
</ul>
</div>